From ac09a94ab7fa5b63976c21bbc74342a40035753b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: David Delavennat <david.delavennat@polytechnique.edu>
Date: Sun, 7 Jun 2026 08:22:48 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] UefiCpuPkg/BaseRiscVMmuLib: fix bitwise-vs-logical typo in
 SetPpnToPte ASSERT

SetPpnToPte() is supposed to assert that no bits of the encoded
physical page number fall outside PTE_PPN_MASK. The intended
expression is the same idiom used a few lines below in
RiscVMmuSetSatpMode():

    ASSERT (!(Ppn & ~(SATP64_PPN)));

but the version in SetPpnToPte() uses bitwise NOT instead of
logical NOT:

    ASSERT (~(Ppn & ~PTE_PPN_MASK));

~(Ppn & ~PTE_PPN_MASK) is zero only when (Ppn & ~PTE_PPN_MASK) is
~(UINT64)0, which is impossible: Ppn was built by shifting Address
right by RISCV_MMU_PAGE_SHIFT and then left by PTE_PPN_SHIFT, so its
low bits are always clear. The assertion therefore always passes
regardless of whether the PPN actually fits, and a too-large physical
address would silently truncate.

In a DEBUG build the assert is still effectively a no-op; in a
RELEASE build it is compiled out entirely. Replace the bitwise NOT
with a logical NOT so the assert behaves as the surrounding code
clearly intended.

No functional change in RELEASE builds. In DEBUG builds the assert
now correctly fires if a caller passes an address whose PPN field
does not fit in PTE_PPN_MASK.

Signed-off-by: David Delavennat <david.delavennat@polytechnique.edu>
---
 UefiCpuPkg/Library/BaseRiscVMmuLib/BaseRiscVMmuLib.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/UefiCpuPkg/Library/BaseRiscVMmuLib/BaseRiscVMmuLib.c b/UefiCpuPkg/Library/BaseRiscVMmuLib/BaseRiscVMmuLib.c
index 34300dc..3415e00 100644
--- a/UefiCpuPkg/Library/BaseRiscVMmuLib/BaseRiscVMmuLib.c
+++ b/UefiCpuPkg/Library/BaseRiscVMmuLib/BaseRiscVMmuLib.c
@@ -240,7 +240,7 @@ SetPpnToPte (
   UINT64  Ppn;
 
   Ppn = ((Address >> RISCV_MMU_PAGE_SHIFT) << PTE_PPN_SHIFT);
-  ASSERT (~(Ppn & ~PTE_PPN_MASK));
+  ASSERT (!(Ppn & ~PTE_PPN_MASK));
   Entry &= ~PTE_PPN_MASK;
   return Entry | Ppn;
 }
